From me at mylesbraithwaite.com  Mon Oct  6 17:44:42 2014
From: me at mylesbraithwaite.com (Myles Braithwaite)
Date: Mon, 6 Oct 2014 13:44:42 -0400
Subject: [GTALUG] Moint just sent a DMCA to a competing OSS
Message-ID: <CA+hskZM5O5+o=F15bRGiE-sHH4TqO+z8Q2AfsxcKPPhjav9vfQ@mail.gmail.com>

Moint (an open source utility for monitoring running processes) issued
a DMCA to GitHub against a competing package, Inspeqtor, written in Go
because they use "the same configuration language that is used in
Monit".

Moint says that Inspeqtor implementation in Go is far from a
"clean-room" and is asking that Mike Perham (the author of Inspeqtor)
"adhere to the GNU Affero General Public License which Monit is
licensed under".

<https://github.com/github/dmca/commit/e8e7a27dd17ad6fe8d53fbb8f6084b560b2d3a29>

